<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[SpectreXS]]></name></author>
<updated>2014-12-03T02:09:33+01:00</updated>
<published>2014-12-03T02:09:33+01:00</published>
<id>http://marioruns.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=375&amp;p=2738#p2738</id>
<link href="http://marioruns.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=375&amp;p=2738#p2738"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Research, Strats &amp; Routing • Lobby Movement Time Chart]]></title>

<category term="Research, Strats &amp; Routing" scheme="http://marioruns.com/forum/viewforum.php?f=17" label="Research, Strats &amp; Routing"/>
<content type="html" xml:base="http://marioruns.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=375&amp;p=2738#p2738"><![CDATA[
Something simple that no one has done before (if they had, lol, then why do people even wonder about &quot;which 120 route has better castle movement&quot;) but that can put an end to the optimal route question once and for all (non LBLJ).<br />Individual comparisons for each route are irrelevant as long as you have this thing. Knowing how much time you lose/gain by lobby movement becomes basically a math problem.<br /><br />The video I made and times I wrote are &gt;&gt;&gt;NOT&lt;&lt;&lt; optimized at all. I made them for myself as a reference when comparing routes, and as a &quot;model&quot; if anyone/group of people want to compile the sick lobby movement strats and make an improved version of this chart.<br />Segments were made using two frames off of the first movement one and last one that mario isn't touching the door.<br />EDIT: The chart is how much it takes from (line) to (column). Mirror and impossible (DW-&gt;UP) times are &quot;0.000&quot;<br /><br />[youtube]https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FZ9Ac_5PBwQ[/youtube]<br /><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FZ9Ac_5PBwQ" target="_blank" class="postlink">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FZ9Ac_5PBwQ</a><br /><br />I put the chart as a image at the start of the video... sorry, I'm ridiculously illiterate on html or whatever so I can't space this correctly &gt;_&lt; here it is anyway just because why the hell not. Looks better in notepad with &quot;tab&quot; spaces<br />. . . . . BOB . . CCM . . DW . . .WF . . .JRB . . Slide . . UP . . .BAS<br />mid-&gt;2.769- 2.135 -2.903 -2.269 -2.436 -3.136 -2.035 -1.835<br />BOB-&gt;0.000- 1.335 -1.568 -3.670 -4.404 -3.437 -2.469 -1.502<br />CCM-&gt;1.201-0.000 -2.269 -3.203 -3.904 -4.104 -3.170 -0.934<br />DW--&gt;1.235- 1.602 -0.000 -3.237 -3.804 -2.870 -0.000 -1.468<br />WF--&gt;3.904- 3.303 -4.037 -0.000 -1.401 -2.202 -3.070 -0.868<br />JRB-&gt;3.871- 3.303 - 4.271 -1.435 -0.000 -1.735 -3.036 -1.635<br />min. 4middle(BAS,BAS,Slide,Slide/WC), 2BOB, 1CCM, 1DW, 1WF, 1JRB, 1to UP, 2to slide, 2to BAS<br /><br />Even with that will people still use routes just based on level preferences? Obviously. But you can at least eliminate the shit movement ones and know the time differences.<br />Didn't even do &quot;to middle&quot; (with lobby light on) timings, if someone wants to do wingcap after non-slide. Cause that's just dumb. <img src="http://marioruns.com/forum/images/smilies/frankerz.png" alt="FrankerZ" title="FrankerZ" /> pc.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://marioruns.com/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1469">SpectreXS</a> — 03 Dec 2014, 02:09</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
