<content type="html" xml:base="http://marioruns.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=360&amp;p=2667#p2667"><![CDATA[
I found this a few weeks back and I was suggested to post this here. So here is my log skip time saver in TTM. I am not sure how much time it would save compared to using the log but, I would guess maybe around 3 seconds but, this could be used multiple times in a run to save more time. Warning: Audio is kinda loud.<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JqiGr0IdCUw" target="_blank">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JqiGr0IdCUw</a><!-- m --><br /><br />You obviously do not need to use my camera setup that just makes it easier. This has a backup strat and a backup strat for the backup strat. If you do not get enough distance and hit the wall you can just do a 2nd/3rd frame wallkick and drift back to grab the ledge. If you try and do the backup strat and get a first frame you can drift and dive to get to the log to recover.<br /><br />I am interested in seeing people's thoughts on this time save and optimizing it if possible. :)<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://marioruns.com/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1542">Vesne</a> — 10 Oct 2014, 08:16</p><hr />
]]></content>
